name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text:
Beautiful place to experience the calm and peace of nature. There's no traffic noise and I can hear insects and animals calling. There were a couple of monkeys but non threatening.

There's a short path that is up slope and it makes the walk more fun and challenging. Spent about 2hours exploring all the routes open to public.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: This is a hidden gem which is located very far from lower peirce reservoir and is quite challenging to come here by foot, the path up here is long and full of up & down steep slopes. The people here are much lesser compared to other parks in this central area, which makes here an ideal place to chill and enjoy the peace & scenery. There are plenty of shaded benches, some pavilions and a few big trees by the waters so you can easily find a spot to sit down and bask yourself in this pristine environment. I enjoyed myself a lot here and would implore you to come here some day!

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: Great place for family picnic or if you want some quiet moments. Place is tranquil and serene. Rather beautiful too. The downside is that the gate will be locked at 7pm, meaning you can’t really hang around and check out the sunset. It is also not easily accessible (which is also a plus point of you want some calm).  Most people drive. Walking can be a challenge as you need to prepare to walk for a long time to reach the reservoir and then back again to the main road. Cycle can be viable but need to be prepared for the steep slopes. But once you reached the reservoir, you will feel that it’s worth the trip.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: Very beautiful scenery. Clean and green. Nice place to bring kids to explore & see monkeys. Just make sure you don't have any food items as there are quite a number of monkeys around

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: A quiet and nice reservoir, it is located quite far from the main road. Most people either drive there, cycling or tracking. There are proper shelter and washroom. You can do a simple picnic with family or friends. However there are quite a few things that are not allow over there and i have attached a picture for the details. It is important to know that the gate has opening hours, don't get lock out.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: Nice place for a picnic. Not many people were here and we can enjoy the food in the nature, in front of the reservoir. Nice paysage, nice view, I really enjoyed this place. We had to pay attention to the monkeys though. We saw 3 of them approaching our location so we hurriedly packed off after eating. Unfortunately, it rained many times for short time and we spend lots of time under one of the shelters.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: Very quiet park with views of the reservoir. Free parking and bathroom here as well. The road to get here has a lot of monkeys to gotta drive slowly. People come here just to relax, sit and wlak, but it may be busy on the weekends as it is a good outdoor date spot

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text:
Nice place to go for a walk. The car park is a distance from the main road. From the car park, you can take a short walk to admire the two reservoirs on either side.
If you're planning to exercise, then it's best to park at Casuarina and walk or jog to the reservoir.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: Beautiful scenery, very quiet. Located quite far from the main road (no public transport) so if you are coming here with kids consider driving or cycling (pretty difficult to book taxi/grab). Walking is totally doable but a bit challenging for younger kids (about 3km from casuarina road carpark via old upper thomson road).

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: It is quite a distance to reach this park. One has to either hike there or drive there. Would recommend to hike or jog there to breathe the freshest air in the morning...

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: I grew up in the area and cycled to Upper Peirce reservoir daily. This beautiful park brings back so many memories. Its scenic, quiet and there's lots of wildlife. You'll love this iconic reservoir.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: It is an excellent walking trail destination starting from the main Thomson road. It can be up-to 30minutes one way walk depending on your pace. It can also be reached by car and parking is free. On way langur or macaques are sure sight. The reservoir itself is very beautiful filled with clear fresh water. Don't miss the Thomson Nature Park while visiting this. No access to park after 7pm.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: Highlight of the Park is the little monkeys. Remember not to feed them. Another beautiful park in Singapore. Well looked after has a pathway to walk around. Good for strollers, little kids and their scooters. Tables and chairs under shade for a picnic or just watch the people walk by.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text:
Read on some board there said this is the 2nd reservoir in Singapore

Have seen the park on map for long and finally there

Monkeys are everywhere, so don’t picnic there. there is a small bridge with stream. Guest what! Saw 4 otters came out from there and went to Thomson Nature Park

There is a public toilet and car park. No so crowded on Saturday afternoon. No shelter walk from Springleaf MRT

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: Such a small and quiet place where you can make your mind empty. Few people here, just grass and  trees and the reservoir. However if you walk here I recommend you to go other place like MacRitchie, cause It will take you more than 40 minutes walking from bus station to reservoir, and the road has lots ups and downs. If you drive or bicycle here it’s worth coming. The end of the road is a dam, and there is a golf club which you cannot enter. I think if the door is open you can directly go to MacRitchie by passing throught the golf club.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: Great park to hang out for cyclists in the morning..though walking is also good but be prepared for super long walk fr main road.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text:
Walking to the reservoir reminds of the song 🎶 it's a long way to Tipperary, it's a long way to go.🎶 It sure is a long way walking in 👣👣👣🚶🚶‍♀️🚶‍♂️🏃🏃‍♀️🏃‍♂️

It's well worth the effort as we stumble across a family Long-tailed Macaques - daddy, mummy and babies, young ones old ones .... The whole kampung was there ! 🐒🐵🙈🙉🙊

Upper Pierce Reservoir is a peaceful and tranquil place to frolic under the sun 🌞🥰 on a lovely weekday afternoon - tons of space, hardly any crowd, perfect during the pandemic season.

We could sit here all day, reading a book 📚 soaking in the scene 🌳 sipping on home-brewed tea ☕ In fact, magnificent views enticing the artist in you 👨‍🎨👩‍🎨   ...  bring along your easel and paints 🎨🖌️ THIS IS THE LIFE! 💖

The perfect place to hide from the hustle and bustle of the fast paced city life 🥰

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: Love  the tranquil and natural feeling of the place. Idyllic and peaceful enough for a romantic picnic. Less people just jogging or exercising than other parks

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: Pleasant park that will slow your heartbeat down. Wide grassy slopes for interesting walks up to the water line. Lots of tame monkeys around.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text:
Just awesome. There are lots of monkey, but they are gentle. No need to feed them as per law.

Serene environment

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: really beautiful reservoir, the view is amazing and strangely calming. nice walk in, as the trees provided shade and there were not as many people walking there as compared to lower peirce reservoir

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text:
I personally love the long walk in. Usually I enter the area via the Upper thomson road entrance near Casuarina prata and just follow the trail all the way till you come up on a gate (left side). This walk in to the gate takes me about 15-20 minutes.

Once you go past the gates, its another 15-20 mins of walking up and down little hills to get to the reservoir.

There are quite a few things I like about this trail. It's relatively serene and quiet. Not many people on the weekday evenings especially the trail from the gate onwards.

The views of the sky I mean just look at the pictures.

And of course the super rewarding view once you come up on the reservoir itself. Certain angles make it look like its not even SG. Love how one time the sunset was making some of the people there silhouettes and I took some photos of that too.

Also I guess cause there are some military camps in the area there are helicopters flying by.

Take note there is a fork in the road at some point. Take time to go to both sides. The views are worth it. Both sides give a different feel.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text:
Have amended the rating from 4 stars to 3 stars because of this particular aggressive monkey. He likes to loiter around the park shelters and car park waiting to pound onto unaware visitors. Do not hold any drinks or food in your hand while walking or resting. He will not hesitate to come up to you and snatch it off your hand.

Parents have to be very careful if you have children accompanying along to the park. Beware of this particular monkey. 2 nasty encounters with him, trying to snatch my lunch. Isn't afraid of humans, aggressive and will confront you face to face.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text:
A 5/5 place for self reflection and enjoy the Murrow to the sky!
Best to come before 10am, when the reservoir might pump in/ out water and distort the mirror and effect!
Recommended!

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: A very beautiful park. The journey in via cycling is tiring with 2 major up hills elevation but very satisfying when you see such a beautiful scenary.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: Best time to visit in the evening, nice sunset view.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: Nice scenery view, very breeze, cooling. Beware cause now alot of monkeys want to grab your food. Becareful when opening car bornet.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text:
Quiet and relaxing place.
There are public toilets and tap water.
The gate closes at 7:30pm and opens at 6:00am. You’ll have to leave there before 7:30pm if you go there by car, otherwise you’ll have to pick up your car next day

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: Long walk to reach. Around 2 km from Thompson Road. No public transport to the park. Car park available. Place is quiet, not many people. Away from roads and housing. Good place to hike in from Thomson road then picnic here. You can also walk to the view point around 1 km from car park.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: It takes a while to reach there and can be a bit dangerous going there but it's worth going since I got to see a cool funny view but just make sure you leave on time since I almost got locked in here xd

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: Worth a trip. About 3km in 1-way.  Fresh air & pretty green sights along the way. Best place to watch sunset and see the two reservoir - Lower Pierce & Upper Pierce together. Many people drives & cycle in. Running or walk-in is possible too. Gate close at 7.30 p.m. daily. Encountered wild boars and monkeys along the way.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text:
Arrived at the Casuarina Car Park at 6.30am and run towards the reservoir. 3KM in and out with some hills in between.

Pictures are from 2 different visits, cloudy/hazy day you can enjoy the zen of reservoir. sunny day, you will be amazed of the sunrise.

Beware of monkeys!

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: Great place for a picnic once you reach (after walking up and down the hilly road). There are many trees and seats and a good toilet. It's a bit dangerous walking there because there is no separation for footpath and cars

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: Great place to explore in the morning, the main gate only open at 6am and close at 7:30pm. The park itself is very short walk across that dam. You can explore another path that will lead you to the PUB pump station.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text:
This is a water reservoir, very good place to exercise for both jogging and cycling especially there are lots of uphills.
Parking lots are quite limited and the path to reach parking is quite narrow, need to pay the additional attention on the cyclists who are riding on the driveways.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text:
Nice views and quiet

Good place to connect the mother earth 🙂

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: It's one of my favourite places to go to if I need some quiet time. Last evening, the family drove down to walkabout just before the place closed its gates. Just walking about, looking at the reservoir, taking in the sunset sights, and enjoying a light breeze....therapeutic😘

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: Beautiful place, fresh air in the morning!

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text:
Hidden gem
Hardly anyone
Nature bath

Recommend for all

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: Really scenic route! I have been in Singapore for quite some time, living very near to this place but it’s the first time I have been here. On one side you have the Lower Peirce Reservoir, and on the other side, the Upper Peirce Reservoir. Really cool. There are also steep, paved hills along the way. Perfect for running or cycling.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: It's a very scenic place to walk with natural view. If you are lucky you can capture the golden sun set in the evening.  You can spend some time with your family in a calm nature. Some monkeys and wild boar emerged from nearby bushes that you have to be aware of.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: It is more of a relaxing place facing the reservoir. Best to come in the evening and early morning. Very windy. Can witness sun set. Can come with family, frens and acquaintances and so on . There are benches for you to sit. Can drive in or by public transport. Can take bus 138, 167, 169, 855, 860, 980.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text:
Nice place to visit and cycling.. little bit harder to go destination if you are trying to cycle or walk there.
Worth place to visit on early morning.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: A very peaceful place with beautiful scenery

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text:
The views were great
Not crowded
Toilets were clean
Ample seats around the water body
Ample parking for cars
Sadly, after walking for 12 km we couldn’t get a cab (Comfort or Grab) to come to pick us. So we had to walk down to a get at the Lower Pierce Reservoir

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: I love the walk in n out to the reservoir. Makes it a great workout n the view when i get to endpoint is worthy reward

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: Great place for morning excercise, although it can bd a liitle crowded. So remember to keep a safe distance from others. Scenery is nice, and can spot a monkey family there too. Enjoyed a walk there.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: Beautiful place, however a long walk from the main road. Expect to walk up and down the hilly slopes before reaching the reservoir. Alternatively, you can cycle or drive. There is a carpark right by the entrance.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: This place is extremely inaccessible by public transport which also meant it was exclusive and is a relatively quieter park to visit. Saw quite a number of monkeys and you’ll also notice at the bottom of the slope towards lower piece there’s a Singapore version of the ‘Blue Boathouse’ which has an aesthetically looking blue door

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: A nice place for hiking with friends. The way before reaching the destination is long and accompanied by many monkeys. Keep any plastic bags away and apply lots of sun block!

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text:
it's a lovely place tucked away from the main roads and buildings. most people drive to get there but if you walk/jog/cycle there, it's worth the calorie burn getting there :)

also, if you drive, there's an auto gate about 2km away from the reservoir that closes at 7.30pm sharp, and it's the only way in or out of the road leading to the reservoir, so you have to leave the reservoir by 7.25pm to be safe, or your car will have to stay overnight until the gate opens at 6am the next day. i've seen a few cars left overnight there, i wonder if anyone has ever got into trouble with their parents/significant others over this.

if you go there on foot, not to worry, there's a small side space next to the gate so you can get in/out without worrying about the 7.30pm time limit. however, do note that the road leading to the reservoir has no street lights whatsoever.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: Perfect place to enjoy sunset.  You can see lot of monkeys along the way. it's a quiet and nice place in Singapore. You can walk, ride a bicycle or drive to the reservoir. If you take the public transport you have to walk around 3 km. The upper Peirce Reservoir park is closed by 7.30pm and you have to exit by the time.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: Beautiful place, very surreal, photos speaks for itself. To get into this park be prepared for a long walk, cycle or drive.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: Nice location and relax environment, away from the busy road. Need to get here by car or cycling, is about 3km from old Upper Thomson Road, good if you like a good walk or a leisure jog. Very shady but quite a bit of monkey atound. Watch out for wildlife big and small.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: Perfect for a morning walk or jog. Not too crowded. Can do yoga or exercises as well. Good place to watch sunrise.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: Very nice place to run in the morning. Parking is free but no shower point available (sadly). Unlike MacRitchie reservoir which you can run along the waterline, here you can run on the road. Sheltered by trees so not so hot.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: We started our walk from Lower Peirce  Reservoir Park then connected to the Old Upper Thomson Road all the way up to the Upper Peirce Reservoir Park. You will be amazed with the beautiful scenery once you arrived at the park. After the long walk, just relax and enjoy the view and peacefulness of the park. Before you head home, can consider  a stopovers at Sembawang Hills Food Center for the famous Seng Huat duck rice or a plate of awesome Char Koay Teow.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: We live near the upper and lower Peirce Reservoirs, but the upper Peirce Reservoirs are much more tranquil, more serenity and much bigger, we enjoyed the fresh air and the beautiful view of the water and the trees.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text:
Very nice place in nature with the water around you. It's very quiet and we were there Sunday and very few people there.
There is also a hiking path through the first close by and it's a great location for bumming or running.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text:
Serene, beautiful place to catch sunset and some wind..

Monkeys came really near us, lol we had to move off

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: Used to be very nice and quite. Can see beautiful sunset. Recently visited found the place grass field was distoryed by wild boar, also known as the "wild swine", "common wild pig"

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: Long road in with not much pedestrian path. Great views. Lots of shade to picnic under at the reservoir.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: Wonderful and very quiet place.Lot of otters and so peacefull environnement, especially during weekdays!

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: The boardwalk that connects Lower and Upper.. Very nice walk.. But be careful and only single file..

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: Lovely reservoir for a stroll or walk... appreciate nature in the midst of pandemic.. highly recommended getaway 👍

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text:
Not touristy, not crowded, hard to reach via public transport but great if you can get there by car or your bike.

Has bike trails leading to the main park.

Lots of monkeys along the way.

Clean, green and quiet. Perfect for a little family picnic.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: Quiet, serene and I can spend my time meditating on the flight of dragonflies, with my mobile, I tried my luck catching them in mid-flight, the thrill was not succeeding but the trying and surprises caught me by the tail. The light breeze and the rows of Casurina trees caught my breath and imagination.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: Nice ride the up and down slope. Beautiful scenery and lots of monkeys too.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: The good thing to view is on the road. Many monkeys. Quiet place. But not very big. Only have a incoming road for cars. Not very good for runners. But good for by cycling

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: Lovely reservoir to relax and enjoy nature in its fullest glory especially during covid-19 when traveling is almost none.👍

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: A truly isolated place for you to relax and see the reservior. Seemed like a countryside, where you dun find much hustle of citylife. I accidentally hump this place and along the way from the thomson road to here, you can see monkeys on the roadside. A worth place to visit if you wish to be in a ppace where less people is around.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: Really nice place to feel in the middle of the nature. It's also a great spot to have a walk, while seeing monkeys and to chill near by the lake. Pretty crowded during the sunny weekends, but if you can make it during the week it's great. Note that it's close over night

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: Nice park with amazing views. Managed to spot some monkeys too!

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: Quiet park. A bit inaccessible and the monkeys are terrible but a beautiful place to relax

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: Get out there serendipity will find you! A lovely green space like many others that Singapore has to offer. Aside from toilets not a great deal there by way of ameneties but lots of nature 🙂🙂

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: Nice stretch of elevation walk before reaching the reservoir

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: Nice place to walk amd enjoy the trees and fresh air in the mornings. Just becareful of monkeys

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: Great place to find nature so surreal by walking in the green and also seeing the great sunset there

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: This is the most peaceful and relaxing place to be.  I have gone there countless number of times. Always take a break there while cycling. Get some morning snack and enjoy the calm waters and great view from the bench. You will enjoy. The route from Ang Mo Kio Bishan Park to Upper Pierce Reservoir is also good for Cycling.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text:
This is quite a small place and quite near Thomson Nature Park.

Couples take wedding photos here too.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: Quite and relaxing place.. Should be good for relaxing picnic.. Wild monkeys are around so need some attention not to be bully by them..

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: One of my favorite nature places. Although there aren’t long trails to walk in, there is enough space to chill and get good views of Bukit Timah hill.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: Situated deep inside forest next to Upper Thomson Road, the park provides an oasis for joggers, cyclist and all who wants to exercise next to nature.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: such a beautiful place and can’t believe i haven’t been here before! we went early morning and the views were amazing ✨ very peaceful and will definitely come back again!

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: Nice and quiet park. One of the only few free parking park in Singapore. Closed at 6pm

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: Nice location for photo shooting. A little bit out of the way. Beautiful and serene environment. Awesome scenic view. Quite place. Nice for strolling and long walks. Good for the kids. Limited parking spaces. Clean toilets.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: Very nice view, although it is not easily accessible, carpark is free.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: It's a good place to go for a walk and peace of mind. However, you may need a transport to be there. Otherwise you may need to take a long long walk to reach there.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: Nice ride to this place, its pretty dark in the after midnight hours hence you gotta have a bright light if you decide to explore this place. Some people come here for fishing too. Met an uncle walking 6 golden retrievers here also at 3am. Quite an adventure in a normally hectic city area.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text:
The Auto Gate closes at 7:30pm SHARP! Not 7:31pm not 7:32pm.

Those driving please take note of this.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: Nice to enjoy the outdoor at upper peirce reservoir park. Good to start early in the morning to see the ray of lights!

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: Beautiful park at Upper #Peirce #Reservoir, in the middle of Singapore water catchment natural reserve.  Good for relaxing walk or jogging.  You may meet some #monkeys.  Do not feed them.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: Nice quiet place to visit, exercise, and relax at. One of the best sunset spot in Singapore.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: Usually bike to get here,  the place is very relaxing and less crowded. If you get lucky, you might see some monkeys on the way

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: Great place to kickstart your morning exercise. Beautiful, serene and lovely reservoir.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: Nice scenic place, but gets very crowded and noisy  over the weekends. Insufficient toilet facilities. Best to visit on weekdays, during the early part of the week. Gets crowded towards the end of the week.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: The sunshine in this park is really lovely. There's no activity areas so u gotta bring your own amusement games.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text:
Great place for picnic, bring the kids and family outing. Loved it. the weather was fantastic and it added a lot more fun to our outing.

The road leading to upper pierce reservoir was beautiful too.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text:
Far from the madding crowd.
Just that the road to go in from Thomson Road is now one-way and narrow. You then turn left to the Park entrance and then all the way to the car park 1-2 km away  - the gate closes at 7:30 pm although the alarm will sound at the car park at 7pm.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: Upper Peirce Reservoir is peaceful places, good for relaxing 🧎🏃🚶for exercise too , 👍

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: A great place to relax among the panoramic view of the reservoir. Albeit hot in the afternoon, bring enough water and shades, although there's free flow of water near the public toilet. Ample parking spaces and handicapped lot.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: A quiet and lovely park. Roadside pavement leading to the main road is being upgraded at the moment. It's a great improvement to road safety. But it also means you can't pull the the side of the road to take a longer look at the monkeys anymore.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: Nice place. Either drive or walk a long way from nearest bus stop.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text:
Free:
Drinking water
Toilet
Parking.

Nice reservoir view for upper and lower peirce.

Many groups of monkeys, some even will obstruct the road path but can scare them off abit by the engine roar or just horn at it. I seen some vehicles became stationary by the monkeys.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: Great place for running and Bicycle. The road has uphill and down it was a good workout!

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: Clean and peaceful park with a nice water view ! Air is fresh. Back to the nature. Lots of monkey to be seen. Relaxing !

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: Beautiful scenery, very quiet with panoramic view on lower pierce reservoir. It's nice to cross the bridge and enjoy the view. Would be a great place to have a picnic by the water unfortunately it's full of monkeys. Another party killer is that you can't swim or even enter the water there.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: Serenity and purely calming. To get best. Relax with your loved one

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: Very beautiful and peaceful place. Went for a short walk with a few of my friends and saw a lot of monkeys around. Do beware not to bring plastic bags of items as it might aggravate them and also do not feed!!

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: Long drive in, but absolutely worth it for the morning air and views that not many places in Singapore can give you. Nice place for wedding shots too.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: Tranquil place for picnic and relaxing. But really nothing and no other activities u May so there! Minus point is it not accessible via public transport.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: Beautiful place to be at peace with yourself. Extremely beautiful surroundings and if you imagine a little, transports you to another world of it's own

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: Nice views awaiting you after a short 30min walk from upper thomson road.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: Nice and peaceful place to cycle and jog while enjoying the nature!!

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: Nice place for an escape from a busy life in the heartland. Amazing view.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: Lovely place, but it's a bit out of the way, hence, the tranquillity.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text:
40 year ago, I visited  this upper pierce reservoir, by curiosity, when I visited the old racing circuits  just next to it , during 1970s, race,and
I turn left with old gate open, to my surprise , it was a hilly road, full of big tall tree, extremely  greenery, for nature lover, like me, slowly I drive through the beautiful scenery with cool fresh  air blowing into my face, was breezy, very quiet and calm your feeling, but have a feeling who built this reservoir??, it like I am in foreigner  country, and I drive till the end, is a car park, facing the wide reservoir, with ripples and glittering from mild sunshine,  ***TO MY SURPRISES, I AM  THE ONLY VISITOR, CAR PARK EMPTY, I WAS THINKING  AM I INTO RESTRICTED  AREA?, AND I WALK AROUND BRIEFLY, I SAW MANY MONKEYS  PLAYING,  HOPPING  FROM BRANCHES TO BRANCHES, IN LOW LYING  TREES,THAT REALLY HAPPY FREELY MONKEYS, IS " BORN FREE " WHERE MOST HUMAN MISS IT*** due to materialistic greed.
I keep going  there,when I am free, this time with my friends, they surprise too!      Always no visitors  within a few years visit, it really calm your minds, to original nature!.
Find out later,approximately  built in **about** 1890 by British colonial  time, before hand over to the Chinese wolf, no building  around  the reservoir, in 100 years old contract,with respect to British goverment law, which they always built anything, which always suit *HUMAN BEING*
I think is true to be ! , to avoid  pollution into the reservoir, as year goes by there is gradual increase in visitors  due to internet existed,
And I visited again, last 3week, I shock saw, many joggers,cyclists, strollers, with the disrespectful  user, putting cheap perfumes, combined  with their smelly sweats, floating in the air, even you are 15 feet away, that is real pollution and the local flooded, is more than the monkeys in stretch of reservoir!,every 2 to 3 minute there is a jogger,jog pass me and the road  have  been converted,  turn  out to be *UGLY SMELLY SCENE* DEEPLY UPSET.😔BY POLLUTED MINDS.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text:
A tiny green space next to a dam that separates the Upper and Lower Pierce Reservoirs. It's accessible by vehicle from Old Upper Thomson Road. If cycle or run you have to negotiate the steep slopes. The distance from the left turn off the Old Upper Thomson Road to the is 3 km approximately.

There is a car park, toilet and water cooler facilities.  The dam is a great spot to watch sunsets. Here one can see the distant transmission towers on the Bukit Timah Hill.

One can sit on a benche and be charmed by the calm body of waters with the reflection of the blue sky and clouds. Meanwhile the playful monkeys are eyeing your food. If energetic, one can walk down the slope on the left side of the dam and touch the edge of the Lower Pierce Reservoir

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text: Nice place for some breather away from the traffic. The entrance is located about 1.3km from casuarina road and going along old upper Thomson road. You can choose to drive, bike or jog into the heart of upper Peirce reservoir which is about 2km from entrance. Just a extra note for first time bikers, the 2km stretch leading to the carpark of upper Peirce reservoir can be dangerous with couple oflong steep slopes, especially the one located just at the start of the entrance. So go slow if you are cycling. For runners, please keep to the opposite of traffic along old upper Thomson road and in upper Peirce reservoir itself. A Must not miss side track in upper Peirce reservoir itself nearing the carpark, located right and is about 1km long is the famous 'air-con' road which by its name always feels like air-con no matter what time of day you are there. Lastly,  remember NOT TO FEED THE MONKEYS ALONG AND IN UPPER PEIRCE RESERVOIR! IT AND OFFENCE AS ONE CAN BE FINED HEAVILY. ALSO BY FEEDING THEM, WE ACTUALLY CREATED PROBLEMS WHERE THE MONKEYS LOSES THEIR ABILITIES TO HUNT FOR THEIR OWN FOOD MAKING THEM AGGRESSIVE TOWARDS HUMANS, ESPECIALLY WHEN ONE IS CARRYING FOOD OPENLY. LASTLY ALSO THE ENVIRONMENTAL ISSUE CREATED...RUBBISH EVERYWHERE. SO REMEMBER TAKE NOTHING AND LEAVE NOTHING.

name: Upper Peirce Reservoir Park
review_text:
(Translated by Google) "Empty Valley You Orchid" drove down a long tree-lined path one by one, and suddenly his eyes brightened. In front of him was a lake and hills, such a quiet and beautiful reservoir! The mountains and rivers are beautiful, the sun is high, and the wind is blowing. . . . If you want to leave worldly troubles behind for a while, here you can find a moment of peace and tranquility; fresh air, pleasant scenery; about three or a few friends, bring your own pot of good tea; this is really unique!

(Original)
＂空谷幽兰＂一一驾车走了一段很长的林荫小径，忽然眼前一亮，前面是一个湖光丘色，那么宁静、秀丽的蓄水池！山清水秀太阳高，好呀好风飘．．．．如果你想暫时抛下世俗的烦恼，这裡可以让你找到片刻的平静祥和；清新的空气、怡人的景色；约三几好友，自备一壶好茶；这裡真的别有洞天！
